# Test fixtures are byte-exact representations of upstream sources and
# must not have their line endings rewritten by Git.
#
# - NHTSA's POST_2010 / PRE_2010 .txt files use CRLF (Finding E in
#   documentation/nhtsa/flat_file_observations.md). The fixture
#   sample_recalls.zip + drift_30col.tsv mirror that line-ending shape
#   so tests exercise the real parser path. Without `-text` here, Git's
#   autocrlf would silently rewrite CRLF → LF in the working copy and
#   break tests/fixtures/nhtsa/build_fixture.py's reproducibility
#   guarantee (the script always writes CRLF; Git would round-trip it
#   to LF on checkout).
# - .zip files are binary; flagged explicitly so a future autocrlf
#   misconfiguration can't corrupt them.
tests/fixtures/** -text
*.zip binary
